SerialDataExplorer is used to be build and installed using the GNU 
standard way calling 

./configure && make && make install

Since SereilDataExplorer is a Java based program there are several 
tools required where Java based programs build and execution relies 
on

	Java SDK 	which is required to set JAVA_HOME
	ant 		which is required to set ANT_HOME

The default install directory is 
on GNU/Linux /opt/SerialDataExplorer,
on Windows(cygwin) C:/Program Files/SerialDataExplorer, 
on Mac /Applications/SerialDataExplorer
First time startup requires usage of the start script in the
installation director, for Windows the executable. 
Afterwards the application gives the capability to 
maintain desktop shortcuts as well as start menu
entries. During runtime a online help is available.
